<Author>Naturak
<Content>A Real Treat! The manager has a great front desk staff. The women we dealt with were attentive, friendly and helpful. In particular, Chelsea went out of her way to talk to us and make sure our stay in Phoenix was an enjoyable one.The hotel has a great free breakfast and large eating area.The pool area is adjacent to the parking lot and by no means luxurious.However, the rooms are Marriott. Clean ,comfortable and quiet.It is far enough from the I17 to allow you to sleep with the windows open (yes they open) although I would ask for a 2nd or 3rd floor room not facing the pool. 
