<Author>TexasDad
<Content>What a deal for families!!!! We have two small kids, 6 and 4. Though it's a tad on the small side, the 2br suite was perfect for our needs. The cost was the same or less than the price of two rooms at similar nearby hotels and has the added convenience of having the kids within the same secured space.The place was clean, the kitchenette with full fridge/freezer and microwave was a good place for snacksdrinks. There are also a stove, oven, and dishwasher which we didn't use.TV has both Nickelodeon and Cartoon Network so mom  dad can sleep a little extra. We stayed 4 nights and had maid service daily.Breakfast was the usual complimentary fare accompanied by a belgian waffle iron which the kids loved. TV in the dining room is set to CNN, so some discretion on seat location may be required.There is a small but serviceable pool. We didn't bring suits because we thought it would be too cool to swim. The daytime temps ~80F found a number of people in the water and their lips weren't blue, so it must be OK.The lobby computer is another great convenience for tourist info, maps (gotta find the local Starbucks!!!), and staying in touch if you must.Staff was very friendly. We got the usual no hablo Ingles from housekeeping, but the front desk was able to communicate our needs without delay.We hadn't stayed at a TownePlace before, but we will definitely look for them in other destinations. 
