<Content>Not so hot. Disapointing service. Little long in the tooth. The two young men running the desk when I checked in at night were too busy being goofs to take care of the customer. They had no interest in providing service. The second evening I was there, I stood at the check in desk for 10 minutes to buy a bottled water. The two same young men were having such a good time together in the back room that I had no one to pay and finally gave up. The rooms are a little long in the tooth. They are okay but not what you would expect from a Marriott property.The young woman running the desk in the morning was attentive. She went out of her way to be nice to the guests. What a difference between the day shift and the night shift. My advice; if you must stay here, check in early and check out early and avoid the two BOZOs!!! 
